const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/profile/";

const title = "GE Profile Refrigerator & Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "GE Profile refrigerator, range, dishwasher & oven repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What GE Profile appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "All current Profile US categories. Refrigerators (PFE-series French door with TwinChill dual-evaporator architecture — PFE28KYNFS being the dominant LA model — PSB built-in side-by-side, bottom-freezer variants, counter-depth French door), ranges (PGB gas freestanding and slide-in, PHS induction, PB electric), wall ovens (PTS / PT smart wall ovens including the WiFi-enabled PTS9200SNSS), dishwashers (PDT smart dishwashers with third rack — PDT845SYVFS, PDT715SYNFS), washers and dryers (PFW870 / PFD870 SmartDispense front-load sets, PTD60 / PTW60 top-load), microwaves (PVM over-the-range and PEM countertop), cooktops (gas, induction, electric in 30-inch and 36-inch widths), and built-in coffee systems on the higher tier. WiFi Connect / SmartHQ app integration is standard across most Profile categories from 2018 forward — we service both the connected and non-connected variants."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does GE Profile refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Common Profile refrigerator repairs in our LA service area: TwinChill evaporator fan motor $245-$385 (the dominant 2017-2022 PFE28 service item — fridge compartment warm with freezer still running normally is the signature symptom); ice maker fill valve $185-$285; ice maker assembly $345-$525; defrost system (heater + thermostat + bimetal) $245-$385; condenser fan motor $285-$425; main control board $345-$525; door gasket replacement $185-$285; water inlet valve $185-$285; LED light panel $185-$285; Turbo Cool fan motor variant $245-$385 on units that have it. Compressor work on an out-of-warranty Profile French door (year 10+) runs $580-$880, and we walk through repair-vs-replace math at that price point — though Profile refrigerators are priced $1,800-$3,500 new, so the math almost always favors repair through year 9-10. Parts ship from GE Appliances' US distribution network (Louisville KY headquarters, regional warehouses), typical 2-5 day lead time for less-common items, common wear parts on the truck for the dominant PFE28 / PSB / PDT / PGB series."
  },
  {
    q: "My GE Profile fridge is warm but freezer is fine — what's wrong?",
    a: "Almost certainly the TwinChill evaporator fan motor on the refrigerator side. This is the most common Profile French door service call in our LA territory and the symptom pattern is distinctive. The TwinChill system uses two separate evaporators — one for the freezer compartment, one for the fresh-food side — each with its own circulation fan. When the freezer-side hardware stays healthy but the refrigerator-side evap fan fails, you get exactly the symptom you're describing: freezer compartment holding setpoint normally (typically 0°F), refrigerator compartment drifting up to 45-55°F over a day or two. The 2017-2022 PFE28 production cohort develops this failure around year 4-5 — bearing wear in the fresh-food evap fan motor, reduced RPM, eventually fan stops entirely. Replacement runs $245-$385 and is typically same-day when we stock the common PFE28 evap fan motors on the truck. Two less-common causes that present similarly: (1) defrost heater failure on the fresh-food evaporator (frost builds up and blocks airflow even when the fan still spins — $245-$385 typical), (2) damper control failure (door between the cold-air sources isn't opening on the fresh-food side — $185-$345). Diagnostic identifies which of the three on-site before parts get ordered. The signature symptom — freezer fine, fridge warm — narrows it to one of these three causes 95% of the time on a Profile TwinChill unit."
  },
  {
    q: "Is GE Profile the same as GE Monogram or GE Café?",
    a: "Same parent manufacturer (GE Appliances, Haier-owned since 2016) but three distinctly different tiers with different parts ecosystems. Hierarchy from base to top: standard GE Appliances → <strong>GE Profile</strong> (entry-premium / smart-features tier — the one your fridge probably is) → <strong>GE Café</strong> (mid-luxury with customizable hardware and matte finishes) → <strong>GE Monogram</strong> (full luxury, built-in, designed to compete with Sub-Zero / Wolf / Miele). Practical service implication: Profile, Café, and Monogram look superficially similar in catalog photos but use different chassis platforms, different control boards, different parts numbering. A Profile PFE28 ice maker and a Monogram ZISS ice maker are not interchangeable. Café and Profile share more parts at the entry-premium level (some control boards, igniters, water valves), but Monogram is more substantially separate. Our techs identify the brand and tier from the model number on the inside-door tag (or under the kickplate, or behind the cabinet panel on integrated units) before any parts get ordered — Profile model numbers start with P (PFE, PSB, PDT, PGB), Café with C (CVE, C2S, CTS, CDT), Monogram with Z (ZISS, ZIC, ZDP, ZDT)."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Haier ownership affect GE Profile parts availability?",
    a: "No — and the question comes up enough that it's worth addressing directly. Haier acquired GE Appliances from General Electric in 2016, but the practical impact on US service availability was minimal. The GE Appliances headquarters stayed in Louisville, Kentucky; Profile engineering, design, and manufacturing remain US-based; the US parts network (Louisville KY backbone plus regional warehouses in Selmer TN, LaFayette GA, and several other locations) continues operating as before. Profile parts ship through GE Appliances' established US channel with typical 2-5 day lead time for less-common items, often same-day or next-day on dominant wear items we stock on the truck (TwinChill evap fan motors, ice maker fill valves, igniters, water valves, common Profile control boards). The Haier transition did not affect the GE Appliances authorized-technician training programs or the OEM parts supply chain. Six-plus years post-acquisition, parts availability for Profile refrigerators, ranges, wall ovens, dishwashers, washers, and dryers remains excellent — comfortably faster than European luxury brands and competitive with any US-supply brand."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you repair GE Profile smart appliances with WiFi issues?",
    a: "Yes, and the WiFi / SmartHQ side of Profile service is worth understanding because it splits into two distinct service trees that we approach differently. <strong>Software / connectivity issues</strong> — app won't connect, SmartHQ shows offline, remote start failing, firmware update stuck — usually resolve without parts: WiFi credential reset on the appliance, app reauthentication, occasionally a firmware push from GE Appliances' cloud. These run $89 diagnostic only if no parts are needed, or labor-only ($120-$180) if extended on-site reset and verification work is required. <strong>Hardware / module failures</strong> — the WiFi communication board itself failing, smart-feature control panel unresponsive, sensor that feeds connected diagnostics (door switch, temperature sensor) failing — these are real parts service. Communication board replacement on Profile units runs $185-$345, smart-feature control panel $345-$525. The diagnostic step separates which of the two categories you're in: if the appliance functions normally without WiFi (door operates, temperature holds, cycle completes), the issue is connectivity-side software, not hardware. If the appliance has broken core functionality AND lost connectivity, it's likely hardware. We tell you which before any parts get quoted. Worth noting: SmartHQ remote-monitoring is cosmetic-not-functional for the appliance itself — the fridge cools whether the app is connected or not — so a WiFi-only failure never blocks the unit's basic operation."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find official GE Profile warranty info?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of GE's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
  }
];

