<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Profile jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Profile service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Profile PFE28KYNFS French door refrigerator, Glendale</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner reported fridge compartment running 48°F over the past 4 days while the freezer held -2°F normally. Milk had spoiled. Set point on fridge was 37°F. Unit was 5 years old, installed in a 2020 Adams Hill renovation kitchen.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2017-2022 PFE28 TwinChill fresh-food evaporator fan motor failure pattern. Fan motor measured open-circuit on continuity test, bearing visibly worn on visual inspection. Freezer-side TwinChill evap and fan tested clean — independent system, why the freezer held normally while the fridge warmed. Defrost system measured within spec; no frost buildup on the fresh-food evap coil.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Fresh-food evaporator fan motor replacement with OEM GE part (in stock on truck for PFE28 family). Verified normal fan operation and cold-air circulation. Verified fresh-food compartment pull-down from 48°F to 38°F over 4-hour soak test. Paired check on defrost heater and thermostat — both clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Profile PGB911SEJSS gas range, Burbank</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Surface burners ignited fine; oven would not light. Owner heard the spark igniter clicking but no flame produced. Unit was 4 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Oven igniter weak — current draw measured below the threshold needed to open the gas safety valve and admit gas to the burner. Spark module functioning correctly (audible click confirmed during attempts). Classic year-3-5 igniter wear pattern across the Profile gas-range lineup, shared with Café and standard GE.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Oven igniter replacement with OEM GE part (in stock on truck — igniters are dominant Profile cooking service item). Verified normal bake and broil light-off, oven temperature pull-up to 350°F within design window. Surface burner igniters tested as paired-check while on-site — all functional.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 60 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Profile PFW870SSPWW SmartDispense front-load washer, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> SmartDispense system stopped dosing detergent on cycle start — owner had to manually pour detergent for the last 3 weeks of cycles. SmartHQ app showed normal supply levels. Cycle otherwise ran normally. Unit was 4 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> SmartDispense detergent metering pump failed — pump motor not engaging when commanded by the control board. Software side checked first (app supply-level reading verified correct, dispense schedule verified active, app-side reset attempted) — confirmed not a software issue. Hardware confirmed: pump motor open-circuit on continuity test. Supply tank seal and supply line both clean.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> SmartDispense metering pump replacement with OEM GE part. Verified normal detergent dosing on test cycle. Verified supply level tracking through SmartHQ app post-repair. Main drain pump (separate component) tested clean as paired check.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

